---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout title="Chess School — Mind's Gambit" description="Train, play, learn, and analyze. Free, ad-free, open-source-powered. Daily tactical puzzles, lessons with grandmasters, 5.94 million puzzles to grind, and our games library of 14.8 million master games.">

<nav>
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo"><img src="/images/logo.jpg" alt="Mind's Gambit" style="height:55px;width:55px;border-radius:50%;object-fit:cover;border:2px solid #c8a84e;margin-left:10px;vertical-align:middle;" /></a>
    <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="/#book">The Book</a></li>
      <li><a href="/watch">Documentary</a></li>
      <li><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
      <li><a href="/chess-school">Chess School</a></li>
      <li><a href="/#about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="/#contact">Contact</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/mouradbouajaja" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="nav-btn">&#9749; Buy Me a Coffee</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</nav>
<a href="/chess-school/classroom" style="display:block;max-width:1100px;margin:1.2rem auto 0;padding:1rem 1.3rem;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#d4af37,#b8932e);color:#0a1a33;border-radius:12px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;text-align:center;font-size:1.02rem;">New: Enter the Live Classroom &mdash; learn with a coach in real time &rarr;</a>

<section class="hero">
  <span class="eyebrow">Mind's Gambit Chess School</span>
  <h1>Chess School</h1>
  <p class="lead">Free. Ad-free. Open-source-powered. Train, play, learn, analyze — built one piece at a time, the way chess is meant to be learned.</p>
  <div class="train-now-wrap">
    <a href="/chess-school/train" class="train-now-btn">
      <span class="train-now-icon">&#9889;</span>
      <span>Train Now</span>
    </a>
    <span class="train-now-sub">One click. Random puzzle. Start sharpening immediately.</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="gm-hero">
  <a href="/chess-school/grandmasters" class="gm-hero-inner">
    <div class="gm-avatar">&#9819;</div>
    <div class="gm-content">
      <span class="gm-eyebrow">Featured &middot; Work with a Grandmaster</span>
      <h2>One-on-one coaching with titled players</h2>
      <p>Curated roster of professional teachers. Start with WGM Maryana Huda &mdash; over a decade of coaching experience, two-time European Youth Champion, FIDE Trainer. New coaches added by referral, not by application.</p>
      <ul class="gm-features">
        <li>Real titled players</li>
        <li>Recordings included</li>
        <li>Mind&rsquo;s Gambit Training Boards</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="gm-cta-wrap">
      <span class="gm-cta">Meet the Coaches &rarr;</span>
    </div>
  </a>
</section>

<section class="grid-section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="section-num">01</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Train</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">Solo practice. Sharpen the eye.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="tiles">
    <a href="/chess-school/puzzles" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9818;</div>
      <h3>Daily Puzzle</h3>
      <p>One fresh puzzle every day. Streak counter. Same puzzle for everyone — solve it before the day ends.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Play today's &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/tactics" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9822;</div>
      <h3>Tactics Trainer</h3>
      <p>Pick a theme — pins, forks, mate-in-2, endgames — and grind rated puzzles. 5.94M to choose from.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Grind by theme &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/tactics?theme=endgame" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9812;</div>
      <h3>Endgame Trainer</h3>
      <p>Master king-and-pawn, rook endings, opposite-color bishops. The endings that decide most games.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Train endgames &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/opening-builder" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9821;</div>
      <h3>Opening Repertoire Builder</h3>
      <p>Build your white &amp; black repertoire. Curated catalog of major openings &mdash; drill mode launching shortly.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Browse openings &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/trivia" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#127919;</div>
      <h3>Chess Trivia</h3>
      <p>Twenty questions on chess history &mdash; from Steinitz to Stockfish, Morphy to Magnus. Brand-new players welcome.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Test yourself &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/featured-games" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#127963;</div>
      <h3>Featured Games</h3>
      <p>Annotated classics from the Romantic era. Morphy&rsquo;s Opera Game, Anderssen&rsquo;s Immortal, the Evergreen &mdash; play through them move by move.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Open the archive &rarr;</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="grid-section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="section-num">02</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Play</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">Face the engine. Or a friend.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="tiles">
    <a href="/chess-school/play" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9823;</div>
      <h3>Play The Mind's Gambit</h3>
      <p>Our engine. Pick any strength from "just learning" to "merciless." All in your browser. <em class="powered">Powered by Stockfish.</em></p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Play now &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a class="tile" href="/chess-school/pass-and-play">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9817;</div>
      <h3>Pass &amp; Play</h3>
      <p>Two players, one device. No accounts, no clock — just the board.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta"></span>
    </a>
    <div class="tile tile-soon">
      <span class="badge badge-soon">Soon</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#128250;</div>
      <h3>Golden Age Chess Films</h3>
      <p>Restored public-domain chess films from the 1930s and earlier — the golden age of the game, preserved and re-mastered.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta"></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="grid-section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="section-num">03</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Learn</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">From the rules to mastery.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="tiles">
    <a href="/chess-school/learn-to-play" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9820;</div>
      <h3>Learn to Play</h3>
      <p>Brand new? Start here. Piece movement, basic rules, first principles of attack and defense.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Start learning &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/games" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#128214;</div>
      <h3>Our Games Library</h3>
      <p>Almost 15 million chess games organized like a ChessBase opening tree &mdash; from the oldest games on record to last week&rsquo;s grandmaster tournaments. Click any opening code and play through the games on the board.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Open the library &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a class="tile" href="/chess-school/basics"><span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">⚔️</div>
      <h3>The Basics: Tactics from Scratch</h3>
      <p>Below 2000, games are decided by simple tactics. The pin, the fork, the discovered attack — the complete toolbox, before you touch an opening.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">&nbsp;</span>
    </a>
<a class="tile" href="/chess-school/pawn-structures"><span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">🏰</div>
      <h3>Pawn Structures: Where Plans Come From</h3>
      <p>The isolani, the Carlsbad, the Stonewall, the Grünfeld center — learn what the pawns want, and the plan writes itself.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">&nbsp;</span>
    </a>
<a class="tile" href="/chess-school/lesson-library"><span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9203;</div>
      <h3>Lesson Library</h3>
      <p><em>Curated curricula by level — three full courses, live now.</em></p>
      <span class="tile-cta">&nbsp;</span>
    </a>
<a class="tile" href="/chess-school/bookstore"><span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">📚</div>
      <h3>The Mind’s Gambit Bookstore</h3>
      <p>Free chess classics — books and articles to read here, at your leisure. Public domain, forever free.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">&nbsp;</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="grid-section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="section-num">04</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Analyze &amp; Resources</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">Look back. Look forward.</span>
  </div>
  <div class="tiles">
    <a href="/chess-school/analyze" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9881;</div>
      <h3>Game Analysis</h3>
      <p>Paste a PGN. Get a computer evaluation of every move. Find your blunders. <em class="powered">Powered by Stockfish 17 NNUE via Lichess Cloud.</em></p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Analyze a game &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/chess-school/resources" class="tile">
      <span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#128218;</div>
      <h3>Chess Resources</h3>
      <p>Curated, open-source-friendly tools and study material. No ads. No upsells. Just the good stuff.</p>
      <span class="tile-cta">Browse &rarr;</span>
    </a>
    <a class="tile" href="/chess-school/position-explorer"><span class="badge badge-live">Live</span>
      <div class="tile-icon">&#9203;</div>
      <h3>Position Explorer</h3>
      <p><em>Set up any position, query the engine — live.</em></p>
      <span class="tile-cta">&nbsp;</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="manifesto">
  <h2>Why Mind&rsquo;s Gambit Chess School?</h2>
  <p>Because the existing chess platforms are loud, ad-saturated, and want your subscription before they want your improvement. Mind&rsquo;s Gambit is the opposite: free at the front, paid only where a human teacher&rsquo;s time is involved.</p>
  <p>Everything here is built around a single purpose &mdash; <strong>your chess improvement</strong>. The puzzles, the engine, the analysis, the lessons from titled players: all of it exists to make you a stronger player, not to keep you scrolling. Transparency isn&rsquo;t a tagline for us; it&rsquo;s the model itself. <strong>No ads. No tracking. No account required to start playing.</strong> Free now, free tomorrow, free for as long as we can keep it that way.</p>
  <p class="manifesto-support">We&rsquo;re a small operation. The hosting, the engine compute, the puzzle library, the hours spent building and maintaining all of this &mdash; it adds up. If Mind&rsquo;s Gambit has helped your chess in any way, you can buy us a coffee. No obligation, no membership, no unlock &mdash; just a way to say thanks if you feel like it. Every coffee helps us keep the lights on and the doors open.</p>
  <a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/mouradbouajaja" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="manifesto-coffee-cta">&#9749; Buy Me a Coffee &rarr;</a>
</section>

<footer class="page-footer">
  <p class="footer-disclaimer">Mind&rsquo;s Gambit Chess School stands on the shoulders of the open chess community. The engine is <a href="https://stockfishchess.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stockfish</a> &mdash; the world&rsquo;s strongest &mdash; free under the GNU GPL v3 license. Puzzles come from the public-domain Lichess Open Puzzle Database (CC0). The board you play on uses the open-source chess.js and chessboard.js libraries. Optional coach commentary on the Analyze page is powered by Anthropic Claude. We&rsquo;re grateful to every contributor whose work makes this possible.</p>
  <p class="footer-credit">&copy; 2026 Mourad Bouajaja. Mind&rsquo;s Gambit Chess School is a production of &copy; MYB Studio LLC.</p>
</footer>
